The paper deals with sublinear algorithms for geometric optimization problems, which are typically studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computational geometry (cs.CG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of conditional sampling as a computational model is also relevant to these areas. Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
